Submitted By:            Combined: Douglas R. Reno (build fix) + still image + tune fix + clap fix
Date:                    2026-03-21
Initial Package Version: 1.21.2
Upstream Status:         Pending
Origin:                  Upstream (PR #1680) + three additional fixes
Description:             Fixes building libheif with SVT-AV1 4.0 and later.
                         Three changes on top of the original build fix:

                         1. Still image mode (SVT-AV1 >= 4.0.0):
                            avif=true, intra_period_length=-1, fps=1/1.

                         2. tune=SSIM fallback to PSNR (SVT-AV1 >= 4.0.0):
                            SVT-AV1 4.x requires CRF for tune=SSIM but libheif uses
                            CQP. Sharp passes tune=ssim by default for .heif() calls
                            which crashes the encoder. Fall back silently to PSNR.

                         3. Set query_encoded_size to nullptr in plugin table (like AOM).
                            SVT-AV1 rounds odd dimensions up for YUV420 subsampling,
                            causing libheif to add a clap box with offset=-(1/2) pixel
                            which Firefox rejects per AVIF spec. AOM avoids this by
                            not registering query_encoded_size at all (nullptr).
                            Internal calls to svt_query_encoded_size remain intact for
                            correct padding of image data passed to the encoder.

